The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Sunday, December 22, 2002 				 Bengal sweep TT golds
																								Hyderabad, Dec. 21 (PTI): Bengal won all three golds in table tennis at the 32nd National Games here on Saturday.																								In the mens singles final, Bengals Sourav Chakraborty beat Soumyadeeep Roy of Rajasthan 11-3, 12-10, 10-12, 11-13, 11-13, 12-10, 12-10. Tamil Nadus S. Raman and Sharath Kamal got the bronze.																								Mouma Das won the womens singles, beating Poulami Ghatak 11-6, 11-7, 9-11, 11-9. Tamil Nadus T. Pradeepa and Anindita Chakraborty of Bengal got the bronze.																								Mouma Das and Saurav Chakraborty bagged the mixed doubles gold, while Shibaji Dutta and Anindita Chakraborty won the silver. Tamil Nadus T. Pradeepa and Sharath Kamal and Bengals Ranabir Das and Poulami Ghatak took the bronze.																								Twin loss in soccer																								Bengals mens and womens soccer teams lost in the finals. While the women went down 0-1 to holders Manipur, the men were done in 1-2 by Punjab.																								Manipur shot into the lead in the 10th minute from a direct free kick awarded by referee Bentala D. Coth of Kerala after an infringement by Bengals Rehana Khatun. 																								 Bengal men took the lead through Mohammed Rahim Nabi in the 71st minute before Saranjit Singh equalised in the 77th. In extra time, Punjabs Gurvinder capitalised on an error by Bengal custodian Prasanta Dora.																								Bengal women clinched the kabaddi gold, beating Andhra Pradesh 26-21. 
